<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-15T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="849" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d849">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.5914/143</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Minister <persName type="to">Egan</persName>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-15T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 15, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>167. Your 342, September 14. While I appreciate the courtesy of
                                Foreign Minister in promptly agreeing to an exchange of notes in
                                regard to church property, I would prefer that the exchange of notes
                                be made here between Mr. Brun and myself, as we were the
                                Plenipotentiaries of our respective Governments in the negotiation
                                and signing of the treaty. I trust the Foreign Minister will
                                telegraph to Mr. Brun the Danish text of the note which you
                                telegraphed me, as I cannot use your translation because it was
                                transmitted to the Department in the confidential green cipher.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>